<div id="review_2404765795" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2404765795" />
    <a title="Anand Gopal" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12512-anand-gopal"><img alt="Anand Gopal" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396120193p2/12512.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2404765795?book_show_action=true">May 27, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anand Gopal" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anand Gopal" href="/user/show/12512-anand-gopal">Anand Gopal</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/34329421-the-shell">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2404765795" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11015690370327925344">This is a terrifying and heartbreaking (and, apparently, realistic) portrayal of life inside Assad&apos;s prisons. The protagonist is a Syrian christian from a communist family who gets sent to the infamous regime prison in palmyra for more than a decade, suffers unimaginable abuse, and somehow survives. It is based on the author&apos;s own experiences. If you want to understand the true nature of the Assad regime you should read this book.</span>
  <span id="freeText11015690370327925344" style="display:none">This is a terrifying and heartbreaking (and, apparently, realistic) portrayal of life inside Assad's prisons. The protagonist is a Syrian christian from a communist family who gets sent to the infamous regime prison in palmyra for more than a decade, suffers unimaginable abuse, and somehow survives. It is based on the author's own experiences. If you want to understand the true nature of the Assad regime you should read this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11015690370327925344" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


