<span id="freeTextContainer7256975865478010023">This is a critical and compelling testament to the harshness and brutality of the Assad regime. Honestly, it was hard to read at times. It is an account of the sadistic physical violence and mental abuse inflicted upon an innocent prisoner on a daily basis by guards for over a decade. This novel is an important piece to understanding the horrors that the Syrian Government is capable of which is responsible for the death of thousands of innocent people.<br/>I can&apos;t say I enjoyed reading it but I am im</span>
  <span id="freeText7256975865478010023" style="display:none">This is a critical and compelling testament to the harshness and brutality of the Assad regime. Honestly, it was hard to read at times. It is an account of the sadistic physical violence and mental abuse inflicted upon an innocent prisoner on a daily basis by guards for over a decade. This novel is an important piece to understanding the horrors that the Syrian Government is capable of which is responsible for the death of thousands of innocent people.<br />I can't say I enjoyed reading it but I am immensely glad I read it. The world should be more aware of the war crimes that Assad has committed. Full disclosure, I received a copy from Paul Starkey but this is my honest opinion of The Shell. </span>
