<div id="review_3881584289" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3881584289" />
    <a title="Bradley Morgan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40614773-bradley-morgan"><img alt="Bradley Morgan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627141254p2/40614773.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3881584289?book_show_action=true">Mar 09, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bradley Morgan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bradley Morgan" href="/user/show/40614773-bradley-morgan">Bradley Morgan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781566560221" href="/book/show/30961992-the-shell">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40614773-bradley-morgan?shelf=2021">2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3881584289" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4900205451569502731">Khalifa’s novel is a thinly-veiled fictionalized account of the brutality and violence endured by prisoners in Syria. Without a trial or just cause, the novel’s protagonist Musa is sent to a desert prison in Syria after being mistaken for a radical Islamist. For nearly 14 years, as Musa is held captive in this personal hell deep in the desert wastes of Syria, he lives his days without speaking and captures everything he see and hears through “mental writing,” a technique developed by Islamists t</span>
  <span id="freeText4900205451569502731" style="display:none">Khalifa’s novel is a thinly-veiled fictionalized account of the brutality and violence endured by prisoners in Syria. Without a trial or just cause, the novel’s protagonist Musa is sent to a desert prison in Syria after being mistaken for a radical Islamist. For nearly 14 years, as Musa is held captive in this personal hell deep in the desert wastes of Syria, he lives his days without speaking and captures everything he see and hears through “mental writing,” a technique developed by Islamists to memorize the Qur’an. Written in the style of a diary, this novel is an exploration of the breadth and scope of the torture and abuse implemented by Musa’s captors, as well as their impact, acting as a commentary and condemnation of Syria’s ruling regime.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4900205451569502731" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


